https://mochajs.org/#running-mocha-in-the-browser
Mocha is a feature-rich JavaScript test framework running on Node.js and in the browser, making asynchronous testing simple and fun.

Mocha does not have a built-in assertion library.
Developers must use a dedicated assertion library in combination with Mocha.

The popular Chai assertion library uses a syntax similar to Jasmine:
Jasmine includes an assertion library that uses an expect-style syntax:

Mocha is younger than Jasmine, created around 2011.
Mocha is not a “complete” test framework, and doesn’t attempt to be.
Instead, Mocha covers the basics and allows developers to extend it with other frameworks.

Chai is BDD/TDD assertion library




